Rating: 4
I made this for Christmas dinner following the suggestions to reduce the amount of butter and sugar added to the sweet potatoes. This worked well and the dish got rave reviews along with a request to make it again for New Year's Day dinner. My mistake was to use softened butter for the streusel topping. I would suggest for anyone who uses a food processor to leave the butter cold to achieve the crumbly texture for the topping. (My first attempt became the basis for a batch of cookies the next day so it wasn't a total waste!) This recipe is easy, delicious and will now be part of our family holiday tradition.

