Rating: 4
The streusel topping is unbelievable. It seems vvery Gourmet magazine-ish, but is very easy! I probably used more than 5 lbs. of potatoes, and added 1 cup of heavy cream and 1 cup of freshly squeezed orange juice, 1 tsp salt, 1 tsp pepper, 1/4 cup light brown sugar to the potatoes. I like more texture, so I did not puree them. The streusel makes A LOT of topping, but it gets crispy and incredibly heavenly in the oven. Next time I make it I will probably use about 2/4 stick of butter.

